Privacy Policy for TubeMetrics - YouTube Analytics

Last Updated: April 11, 2026

1. Introduction

TubeMetrics ("we," "our," or "the App") is a YouTube analytics application that provides channel statistics, growth tracking, and performance insights. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information.

2. Information We Collect

2.1 Information You Provide

Channel names or IDs you search for
Channels you save to your Favorites list
2.2 Automatically Collected Information

Device type and operating system version
App usage data (screens viewed, features used)
Advertising identifiers for ad personalization
Crash logs and performance data
2.3 Information We Do NOT Collect

Personal names, email addresses, or phone numbers
YouTube account credentials or login information
Location data
Contacts, photos, or files from your device
Financial or payment information
3. How We Use Your Information

We use collected information to:

Display YouTube channel statistics and analytics
Save your favorite channels locally on your device
Serve relevant advertisements
Improve app performance and fix bugs
Analyze app usage patterns to enhance features
4. Data Storage

All user preferences and favorite channels are stored locally on your device. We do not store your personal data on external servers. Clearing the app data or uninstalling the app will remove all locally stored information.

5. Third-Party Services

The App uses the following third-party services that may collect data:

Google AdMob — for displaying advertisements. AdMob may collect device identifiers and usage data for ad personalization. See Google's Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
Google Play Services — for in-app updates and core functionality. See Google's Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
6. Advertising

The App displays banner advertisements and rewarded video advertisements powered by Google AdMob. You may opt out of personalized advertising through your device settings under Google > Ads > Opt out of Ads Personalization.

7. Children's Privacy

TubeMetrics is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us and we will delete it.

8. Data Security

We implement reasonable security measures to protect information processed by the App, including encrypted network communications (HTTPS) and local-only data storage. However, no method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

9. Your Rights

You have the right to:

Delete all locally stored data by clearing the app data or uninstalling the App
Opt out of personalized advertising through your device settings
Request information about what data is collected
10. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected by updating the "Last Updated" date above. Continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

